txt.en: Warg-riders of Moria can be found at Zaghúth.\n\nYou should defeat Warg-riders of Moria at Zaghúth.

You have defeated many Warg-riders of Moria at Zaghúth.
Although the Redhorn Pass remains blocked, your defeat of the Warg-riders of Moria has loosened the Orcs' grip on Barazinbar.
Defeated Warg-riders of Moria at Zaghúth ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

While exploring the heights of the Redhorn Pass, you have come across the Orkish encampment of Zaghúth. Within Zaghúth, a small company of Warg-riders of Moria keep watch on the pass and ensure that no unwanted guests enter the realm of Azog.\n\nYou should defeat the Warg-riders of Moria at Zaghúth.
On the snowy slopes of Barazinbar, goblin warg-riders guard the blockade at Zaghúth.
